noun.description: A cinquefoil (genus Potentilla), which typically has compound leaves of five leaflets. Now chiefly US and rare.
An ornamental design resembling this leaf; = "cinquefoil". rare.

origin: Old English; earliest use found in Bald's Leechbook. From classical Latin quīnquefolium cinquefoil (the plant), in post-classical Latin also ornamental design resembling this leaf, use as noun of neuter of quīnquefolius having five leaves from quīnque- + folium leaf.
